# Turan, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Turan () is a rural locality (a selo) in Tunkinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 711 as of 2010. There are 20 streets.
Geography
Turan is located 34&nbsp;km west of Kyren (the district's administrative centre) by road. Khoyto-Gol is the nearest rural locality.
